

**Elemental Chaos** is a dynamic 1v1 card game where players battle using elemental forces and special abilities!  
The project is built with **Python** and **Flask**, with simple web interface for gameplay interaction.

> 🎯 This project is a **collaborative effort** between the user and **ChatGPT**, combining human creativity with AI assistance.

---

## 🚀 Project Overview

- **Elemental Chaos** simulates an exciting turn-based card battle.
- Each player has a hand of cards belonging to the four elements: **Fire**, **Water**, **Earth**, and **Air**.
- Special action and wild cards introduce chaotic effects, shifting the strategy constantly.
- The objective: be the first to play all your cards or outlast your opponent.

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- **Python 3**
- **Flask** (Web framework)
- **HTML5** (Templates)
- **CSS3** (Basic styling)

---

## 🎮 Main Features

- 1v1 match: **Human vs CPU**
- **Basic cards** (elements + numbers) and **special cards** (wild & action cards)
- Special effects: **Flood**, **Tornado**, **Earthquake**, **Firestorm**, **Chaos Orb**, **Elemental Swap**, and **Shields**.
- **Declared elements** after playing wild/action cards to control the next moves.
- Full deck management: **draw**, **play**, **discard**, **shuffle**.
- Simple web interface to interact with the game (via `/game` page).
- Game automatically detects win conditions and declares the winner.
- Designed for quick iteration and easy future expansion.

---

## 📖 Future Enhancements (Planned)

- Improved UI and animations.
- Multiplayer (online player vs player).
- Score tracking and stats.
- Expanded deck with new elemental types or combos.

